President Obama and Vice-President Biden were briefed on the BP Deepwater Horizon oil spill by several senior administration officials, including Secretary Napolitano, Secretary Chu, Secretary Salazar, Administrator Jackson, Administrator Lubchenco, and Carol Browner. The briefing included updates on the number of personnel and resources involved in shoreline protection and cleanup, as well as containment efforts and plans to increase oil capture capacity. The briefing also covered hurricane projections and potential impacts on the response, seafood safety, the use of dispersants, and additional environmental impacts on wildlife and coastal habitats.